    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-07T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="383"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1001</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-07T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 9, 10.15
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2185. For <persName corresp="#p_HL1">Harrison</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName>:</p>
                <p>8. Leaving to-night for Vienna. Safe-conduct granted to me for the round trip
                    although Austrian Legation had cognizance of President <persName
                        corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s message and final resolution.</p>
                <p>In view <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s telegram 2124, November
                    26, 6 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d383fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_322">p. 322</ref>.</note>
                    suggest you enquire of <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName> in The
                    Hague his views concerning <persName corresp="#p_KCM1">Károlyi</persName>’s
                    reliability.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
